<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-10-06T11:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-10-06T11:29:00-05:00" n="652" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d652">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.156/261</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-06T11:00:00-05:29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 6, 1917, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The time for filing claims by Ports Company expired last Monday. This
                            week President and commission have devoted to matter and have offered
                            settlements by which Cuban Government pays for bonds at par and turns
                            over assets of company to stockholders. Understand London interests
                            being consulted by cable.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>